This is a prime time probe into the circumstances surrounding
the death of Jimi Hendrix.  Thankfully, at least half of the
story deals with Jimi's life.  Chas Chandler and Noel Redding
add substance to this program, which questions how the official
investigation was conducted.  Long time girlfriend, Cathy 
Etchingham and Jimi's last lover Monika Danneman are at odds
with each other over different issues.  This report asserts
that the Hendrix estate may be the cause of all this friction.
One thing is for certain - with factual inaccuracies and
trite cliches, the script for this report stinks. 
Sort of a VH1 meets Court TV meets Dateline NBC.  
Jack Cafferty hosts
